HEADWORD: Heliometry
<hw>He`li*om"e*try</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The apart or
practice of measuring the diameters of heavenly bodies, their relative
distances, etc. See <er>Heliometer</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

